  "prompt": "What on earth should I be instead of a fashionista if I'm an artist that draws?",
  "response": "If you're an artist who draws and want to define yourself beyond the term \"fashionista,\" there are plenty of creative and fitting labels or roles you could embrace that highlight your artistic identity. Here are some ideas:\n\n1. **Visual Artist** - A broad, professional term that encompasses all forms of visual creation, including drawing, painting, and illustration.  \n2. **Illustrator** - If your focus is on creating illustrations, this is a clear and specific title.  \n3. **Sketch Artist** - Perfect if your specialty lies in sketching or drawing by hand.  \n4. **Creative Visionary** - A more abstract and aspirational term that reflects your imaginative process.  \n5. **Storyteller (Visual)** - If your art tells stories or conveys narratives, this could be a meaningful descriptor.  \n6. **Concept Artist** - If you create concept art for ideas, characters, or worlds, this is a great fit.  \n7. **Graphic Artist** - If your work includes digital or graphic elements.  \n8. **Artisan** - A term that emphasizes the craftsmanship and skill behind your work.  \n9. **Designer** - If your art leans into design, whether for fashion, products, or other media.  \n10. **Creative Explorer** - A playful way to describe your journey of artistic discovery and experimentation.  \n11. **Imaginist** - A unique, made-up term that emphasizes your imagination and creativity.  \n12. **Visual Storyweaver** - A poetic way to describe how your art weaves together images and narratives.  \n13. **Doodle Master** - If whimsy and playful sketches are your thing, this is a fun and approachable title.  \n14. **Art Alchemist** - Suggests transforming ideas and materials into something magical.  \n15. **Aesthetic Architect** - If you\u2019re focused on creating beauty and structure through your art.  \n\nChoose a term that resonates with your artistic style, process, or goals. You can also mix and match or create your own unique title to reflect your individuality!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
